  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6554.34 sitting just below the massive negative gamma wall at 6550 (-16.7B), dealers are likely buying aggressively into this dip as their short gamma position forces them to chase price lower, creating amplified downside momentum. The PIN regime confirms dealers are positioned long gamma overall, but the proximity to max negative gamma at 6550 means any break below triggers accelerated dealer buying that could spark a sharp reversal bounce toward the 6580 positive gamma wall (+19.4B). Watch 6550 as the critical inflection point - a hold above keeps us in the stabilizing zone between positive gamma strikes, while a breakdown below 6550 unleashes dealer buying pressure that typically creates violent mean reversion back toward 6565-6580.",
